<br>
Phantom Armor<br>
Burnout IV<br>
Muzzle of Mardu<br>
Shock of Fiery Blades (I've seen this one for 2K)<br>
<br>
and one I know I can't afford -<br>
<br>
Transon's Elemental Renewal<br>
<br>
I haven't seen any of these for sale in the bazaar so I assume they are expensive or very expensive.  The most I've paid for any of my spells as of yet is 1K and that was for Velocity. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uomegasyphon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>omegasyphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 274<br> <font color=#333333>(8/23/02 8:29:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1490.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   comment</span><hr size=1> you mean phantasmal armor cause phantom armor is avendor bought spell in FV. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umenarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Menarion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(8/23/02 8:48:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1490.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   comment</span><hr size=1> Yep. Thanks for the correction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udurash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Durash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#333333>(8/23/02 10:07:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1490.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> Renewal isn't dropping enough to really become available for sale yet.  If it is, you're right, you won't be able to afford it - and there are a lot of things that will be more useful to you for now than putting that spell into the bank.  At 51st, don't even worry about it.  Just get Infusion and use that.  Probably six or so months from now Renewal will start to pop up at not-quite-so-insane prices, and by then your level will be enough that you will want to start thinking about it, and you'll probably also have the cash for it.<br>
<br>
Armor spell...I don't remember, is that the same one that matches the lvl49th spell and uses a pearl?  I don't think I've ever even seen that one, much less seen it for sale, and it really never was necessary (just carry extra agates with you).  If you see it cheap, buy it, but otherwise don't worry about it.<br>
<br>
Burnout IV should be 1k-3k at the Bazaar on a good day, 8k+ if some nutcase thinks he's the only one with a copy.  Take a group or two down to the Juggs in Seb and you'll probably have a good chance at scoring a copy.<br>
<br>
Muzzle - same as BO4.  Rarity is about the same, cost is about the same.  If you have BO4 already, you really don't need this spell until the haste cap gets fixed, but it's still good to hand out to other pet classes.<br>
<br>
Shock - 2k is actually not a terrible price.  If you wait it out, it'll keep coming down.  I've seen it for 1k often on Druzzil, and I recall once seeing it for 500p (vendor was empty when I found him, though).  <br>
<br>
Best of luck - <br>
